line_1: Yet age by long experience well informed,
line_2: Well read, well temper'd, with religion warmed,

line_1: Should think they better were inform'd,
line_2: This was deny'd, it was affirm'd;

line_1: Should think they better were inform'd,
line_2: The herds an' hissels were alarm'd;

line_1: Should think they better were inform'd,
line_2: The rev'rend gray-beards rav'd an' storm'd,

line_1: Like diff'rent bodies, with one soul inform'd,
line_2: Like brethren, in the self-same int'rests warm'd,

line_1: Panting for Knowledge, rests not till inform'd,
line_2: The Soul, with great and manly feelings warm'd,
